st for information (requisitions).","details":{"body":"\u003cp\u003eYou can use the ‘reply to requisition’ function within the portal to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003eattach new or replacement documents directly to your application, allowing your application to be processed quicker\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003eadd relevant information to a pending application at any time using the reply to requisition function, even when an application has been sent by post and you need to submit supporting documents\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003esend a text response and avoid requests for information (requisitions) by providing supporting information before we raise the request - partial replies can also be submitted using this function.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOur casework team will respond to queries and deal with your replies.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWatch our short \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.gotostage.com/channel/2c2b67c56c2b4603acac3b460bd42695/recording/df198fbb04cc4a07b606bd02df5bbaf3/watch\"\u003evideo guide\u003c/a\u003e for help using this function.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you submitted your registration application through Business Gateway, use your case management system to respond to the requisition.\u003c/p\u003e\n","image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5cfe6312ed915d09a2eb034b/reply-to-requisition.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5cfe6311ed915d0974d2a9ca/reply-to-requisition.png","alt_text":"A screenshot of the reply to requisition function overlaid onto a graphic of a laptop computer","caption":"","credit":""},"change_history":[{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2019-06-10T14:04:52.799Z"}]}}